world <- map_data("world")
data <- read_csv("CompleteData.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(

data_2016 <- read_csv("CompleteData_2016.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   Series = col_character(),
##   `Series Code` = col_character(),
##   `Country Name` = col_character(),
##   `Country Code` = col_character(),
##   `2016 [YR2016]` = col_character(),
##   long = col_double(),
##   lat = col_double()
## )
reduced_data_2016 <- filter(data_2016, data_2016$`Series Code`=="SE.PRM.CMPT.ZS")
reduced_data_2016$`2016 [YR2016]` <- as.numeric(reduced_data_2016$`2016 [YR2016]`)
reduced_data_2016$long <- as.numeric(reduced_data_2016$long)
reduced_data_2016$lat <- as.numeric(reduced_data_2016$lat)

g<-ggplot()+
  geom_tile(data=reduced_data_2016,
            aes(x=long, y=lat,fill=reduced_data_2016$`2016 [YR2016]`),
            width=5, height=5,alpha=.5)+
  scale_fill_distiller(palette="Spectral")+
  theme_void()

g <- g+geom_path(data = world, aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group))

g + coord_map(xlim=c(-97,-33),ylim=c(-60,14))

# SE.PRM.TENR is the variable we will using. varied by male and female: SE.PRM.TENR.FE, SE.PRM.TENR.MA
# we are using five countries-- Bolivia, Chile, Colombia, Peru, Venezuela

both_genders_PrimNetEnrollment <- filter(data_all_years, data_all_years$`Series Code`=="SE.PRM.TENR")

both_genders_PrimNetEnrollment$`2012 [YR2012]`<- as.numeric(both_genders_PrimNetEnrollment$`2012 [YR2012]`)
both_genders_PrimNetEnrollment$`2013 [YR2013]`<- as.numeric(both_genders_PrimNetEnrollment$`2013 [YR2013]`)

both_genders_PrimNetEnrollment$`2015 [YR2015]`<- as.numeric(both_genders_PrimNetEnrollment$`2015 [YR2015]`)
both_genders_PrimNetEnrollment$`2016 [YR2016]`<- as.numeric(both_genders_PrimNetEnrollment$`2016 [YR2016]`)

female_PrimNetEnrollment$`2011 [YR2011]`<- as.numeric(female_PrimNetEnrollment$`2011 [YR2011]`)

female_PrimNetEnrollment$`2013 [YR2013]`<- as.numeric(female_PrimNetEnrollment$`2013 [YR2013]`)
female_PrimNetEnrollment$`2014 [YR2014]`<- as.numeric(female_PrimNetEnrollment$`2014 [YR2014]`)
female_PrimNetEnrollment$`2015 [YR2015]`<- as.numeric(female_PrimNetEnrollment$`2015 [YR2015]`)

male_PrimNetEnrollment$`2011 [YR2011]`<- as.numeric(male_PrimNetEnrollment$`2011 [YR2011]`)
male_PrimNetEnrollment$`2012 [YR2012]`<- as.numeric(male_PrimNetEnrollment$`2012 [YR2012]`)
male_PrimNetEnrollment$`2013 [YR2013]`<- as.numeric(male_PrimNetEnrollment$`2013 [YR2013]`)
